
Place @eggs{2} in a small #pot{} and add enough water to cover. Bring to a
boil, then immediately cover and turn off heat. Let stand ~{11%minutes}, then
carefully drain.

Run under cold water until cool to the touch. Peel and slice eggs into rounds.

While eggs cook, wash and dry all produce.

Dice @Persian cucumber{1} and @Roma tomato{1} into ½-inch pieces. Halve and peel
@shallot{1}; thinly slice one half. Quarter @lemon{1}. Peel and finely chop or
grate @garlic{1%clove}. Trim and slice @zucchini{1} crosswise into ½-inch-thick
rounds.

> For 4 servings, thinly slice whole shallot instead of halving.

== Israeli Salad ==

In a #medium bowl{}, combine cucumber, tomato, sliced shallot, juice from half
the lemon, and a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tbsp}. Season with @salt{} and
@pepper{}.

== Harissa Garlic Sauce ==

In a #small bowl{}, combine @sour cream{4%tbsp}, ¼ tsp @harissa powder{1%tbsp}
(you'll use more in the next step), and a pinch of garlic. Add @water{} 1 tsp at
a time until mixture reaches a drizzling consistency. Taste and add more garlic
if desired. Season with salt and pepper.

> For 4 servings, use ½ tsp harissa powder.

== Zucchini ==

In a #large bowl{}, toss zucchini with a large drizzle of olive oil, 1 tsp
harissa powder (be sure to measure), salt, and pepper.

Heat a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add zucchini and cook until browned
and tender, ~{2-3%minutes} per side.

> For 4 servings, use 2 tsp harissa powder.

== Assembly ==

Meanwhile, halve @whole wheat pitas{2} crosswise to create pockets. Wrap in
damp #paper towels{} and microwave until warm and pliable, ~{30%seconds}.

Spread insides of pita pockets with @hummus{4%tbsp}, then fill with zucchini,
eggs, a bit of salad, and harissa sauce. Drizzle with @?hot sauce{1%tsp} if
desired. Divide pita pockets between plates and serve with remaining lemon
wedges and salad on the side.